^-|CP||FP||at|^B@2^Z@3When your partner makes a splinter bid, your best holding is ^*Bfour or five cards^*N along with very little (if any) high card strength in partner's short suit. Three low cards is an excellent holding. Contrary to what many players believe, A-x-x is not the perfect holding in partner's short suit. You'd much prefer to have your Ace in partner's longer suit as you will see in the next example.|
